{
  "new_problem": "Prove that for any positive integer n, n is divisible by 3 if and only if the sum of the digits of n (in base 10) is divisible by 3.",
  "proof_sketch": "Step 1) Write n in decimal form: n = a_k × 10^k + a_{k-1} × 10^{k-1} + ... + a_1 × 10 + a_0, where each a_i is a digit from 0 to 9.\nStep 2) Observe that 10 ≡ 1 (mod 3), since 10 = 9 + 1 and 9 is divisible by 3.\nStep 3) By properties of modular arithmetic, 10^m ≡ 1^m ≡ 1 (mod 3) for any non-negative integer m.\nStep 4) Substitute into the expression for n: n ≡ a_k × 1 + a_{k-1} × 1 + ... + a_1 × 1 + a_0 (mod 3).\nStep 5) Simplify: n ≡ a_k + a_{k-1} + ... + a_1 + a_0 (mod 3).\nStep 6) Therefore, n ≡ 0 (mod 3) if and only if the sum of digits a_k + a_{k-1} + ... + a_0 ≡ 0 (mod 3)."
}
```

